   \ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) color(yellow)
   ! type(output) intens(low ) caps(off) just(asis ) color(white)
   Â¦ type(text  ) intens(high) color(white)
   ` type(text) intens(low ) caps(off) just(asis ) color(turq)
)Body
+---------------------------% TSO/E-Mail Tutorial +-----------------------------
%Command ===>_zcmd
`
`      The\Answer`option is used to send an anwser to the sender of the
`      selected message.  This option is a fast path to the SENDMAIL
`      command with the receiving node and userid predefined with the node
`      name and userid of the person who sent you the message.  The subject
`      is also predefined with the subject of the original message.
`
`      The\Delete`option is used to delete the message and any associated
`      file that accompanied the message.  Note that you will be prompted
`      to confirm the deletion of the file so that you can keep the file
`      even though you have deleted the message, or delete the file and
`      retain the message. Use of\DN`will delete the message and file
`      without any prompting.
`
`      The\Delete`option may also be specified as\DM`to only delete the
`      message, or as\DF`to delete the file and retain the message.
`
`      The\Edit`option will invoke ISPF Edit to allow the user to edit
`      the saved message.
)End
